A Vulkan-based translation layer for Direct3D 10/11 which allows running 3D applications on Linux using Wine.

== Installation ==
{{important|DXVK is not part of the gentoo repository.}}

=== Requirements ===
1. app-emulation/winetricks-9999
2. media-libs/vulkan-loader

=== Installation for WINE ===

'''1. Download lastest DXVK from release page and extract it.'''<br />
https://github.com/doitsujin/dxvk/releases

'''2. Define your WINEPREFIX'''<br />
`export WINEPREFIX‚Äç=<PATH>`

Where `<PATH>` is path to your wineprefix.

- Default WINEPREFIX is located in /home/$USER/.wine
-- It's recommended to create .wine-32 or .wine-64 for different architectures.

'''3. Install'''<br />
Invoke `winetricks --force setup_dxvk.verb` <b><u>from a non-root user</b></u> in DXVK DIR that you downloaded in step 1.

=== Installation for Lutris ===

'''1. Download latest DXVK from release page and extract it.'''<br />
https://github.com/doitsujin/dxvk/releases

'''2. Install'''<br />
Move `/x64` AND `/x32` to `/home/$USER/.local/share/lutris/runtime/dxvk`.

